Name: pythtb
Version: 1.7.2
Summary: Simple solver for tight binding models for use in condensed matter physics and materials science.
Home-page: http://www.physics.rutgers.edu/pythtb
Author: Sinisa Coh and David Vanderbilt
Author-email: sinisacoh@gmail.com  dhv@physics.rutgers.edu
License: gpl-3.0
Download-URL: http://www.physics.rutgers.edu/pythtb
Description: The tight binding method is an approximate approach for solving for the electronic wave functions for electrons in solids assuming a basis of localized atomic-like orbitals.
Keywords: tight binding,solid state physics,condensed matter physics,materials science
Platform: UNIX
Platform: MAC OS X
Platform: Windows
